#META# writingSupportDetails: lacunae :: pasted into Mirza Khwaja Muhammad’s notebook
#META# writingSupportNotes: Incomplete (top, bottom and some parts of the margins are missing), black ink.
#META# foldLinesCount: 12
#META# foldLinesAlignment: horizontal
#META# contentSummary: A fragmentary letter sent to a high official, probably situated in Firuzkuh either at the time of Ghurid or Khwārazmshāhī rule. The writer has travelled to Firuzkuh several times but was denied access to the recipient. He wishes to return to Firuzkuh and might be seeking employment in the court.
